<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-01-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="749" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d749">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-01-06"><hi rend="italic">January 6,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Eddy requests that a formal statement declaring that the Department
                            of State has been unable to communicate direct with Vladivostok be sent
                            to him as evidence in assisting the postponement of the prize cases
                            before the admiralty court.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>